    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2005 Porsche 911 Carrera (997.1) features the legendary 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six, delivering linear power delivery through a crisp 6-speed manual transaxle. The chassis remains taut with its MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension, offering exceptional lateral grip and communicative steering feel. Recent service includes an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a new rear main seal, ensuring the M96 powerplant's longevity. Equipped with four-piston monobloc Brembo calipers and cross-drilled rotors, the braking system provides consistent thermal management and bite. A driver-focused example with a clean mechanical bill of health, ready for the twisties.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 38
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Used vehicle in good condition. Maintenance records available. Reliable performance. Clean title.",
